---
import SectionLabel from './SectionLabel.astro';
---

<section id="results" class="border-t border-rule py-20 sm:py-28">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 sm:px-10">
    <SectionLabel index="06" label="What to expect" />
    <h2 class="display mt-8 max-w-2xl text-[2.25rem] leading-[1.05] sm:text-[3rem]">
      Nothing but <em class="display-italic">net</em> savings.
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-14 grid gap-x-16 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="border-t-2 border-ink pt-5">
        <p class="num text-6xl text-accent sm:text-7xl" style="font-weight:500">30&ndash;50<span class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl">%</span></p>
        <p class="label mt-3 text-ink-faint">Target savings range</p>
        <p class="mt-3 max-w-xs text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
          Agreed as a firm percentage in week one, then measured against your own baseline.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-10 border-t-2 border-ink pt-5 sm:mt-0">
        <p class="num text-6xl sm:text-7xl" style="font-weight:500">21<span class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl">d</span></p>
        <p class="label mt-3 text-ink-faint">Audit to live dashboard</p>
        <p class="mt-3 max-w-xs text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
          Fixed timeline. Attribution instrumented, levers shipped, monitoring handed off.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-16 max-w-2xl border-t border-rule pt-8 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
      <span class="label text-ink-faint">How we measure &mdash;</span>
      every figure is compared like-for-like against a baseline we sign off together before any change
      lands. No marketing estimates, no cherry-picked windows. Miss the agreed number and you don't pay.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
